This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it focuses on robotic grasping and the use of touch sensing to improve grasp outcomes. Computer Vision (cs.CV) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of vision in combination with touch sensing. Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) are also possible sub-categories as the paper evaluates deep neural network models for grasp outcome prediction. Finally, Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible as the paper discusses the importance of touch sensing for successful grasping, which is relevant to human-robot interaction.
